# Planning for the September Sac Meetup. 
Tentative Dates: Sat 26th or Sun 27th. 
Alternative: Tues 29th - later evening (7/8pm+)

## Meeting Space
I may be able to get the same library space at Sylvan Oaks again. It's free and has WiFi. The downsides: Must be a Saturday before 5pm. I know some people work then.

I investigated "The Trade: Coffee and Coworking". 
They have a large room (40 people) with WiFi. Cost is $50/hour for the group. No one need be a member. Post-meeting it's $8/hr/person.

HackerLab Sacramento is not open weekends. Membership appears to be required.
All of the other Coworking spaces I looked at require a membership and/or don't have a large meeting space.

I am open to suggestions for alternate meeting spaces. I see several requirements:
1) Free or low Cost (< $10/person for the event)
2) Quiet(ish) meeting space
3) WiFi
4) Ideally open Sunday afternoon so we can get more folks or in the evening.

## Topics and/or Activities
I'd like to collect topic ideas for presentations, if that's what we want. Maybe less stuff this time? I'd like feedback on the material we went over - too much? Too Little? More of the same?
Do we just want to do some pair programming with no presentations?

### Random Possible Topics:
Big-O Notation (I can present)
Programming Interview Skills or Questions (Need a presenter)
<Your Suggestion Here>
